[A total of 9 of 29 cases developed hemolytic uremic syndrome (HUS) (31 percent), a quite high number. Usually less than 10 percent will develop this complication which can be linked to inappropriate early use of antimicrobials. This may be a strain that produces higher amounts of Shiga toxin. - Mod.LL

